article.headline: Oral Roberts 74, Chicago St 65
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 25 points and Ken Tutt added 15 to help give Oral Roberts a 74-65 victory over Chicago State on Monday. The loss was Chicago State's tenth straight. Jonathan Bluitt scored 10 points for Oral Roberts (6-7, 1-0), and Yemi Ogunoye led the team with nine rebounds. The two teams were tied 28-28 at the half, but Chicago State (1-12, 0-2) was 1-for-10 from the 3-point line in the second despite shooting 12-of-14 free throws. Oral Roberts shot 65.2 percent from the free-throw line for the game, including 14-of-20 in the second half. Royce Parran led the Cougars with 19 points, and David Holston added 17.
